main event: The report describes multiple sightings of unidentified objects over several cities in the United States from March 18 to March 25, 1963.
interesting points: The objects were observed in various locations including south and north of the cities, at different altitudes ranging from 5 to 87 degrees above the horizon.
The objects were observed at different times of the day, from early morning to late evening.
The report includes precise times and locations for each sighting, suggesting a systematic documentation of the UFO activity.
The objects were described as moving, with no mention of any sound or exhaust being observed.
The report does not provide any additional details about the objects' appearance or behavior, leaving the nature of the sightings unexplained.
location: Multiple cities in the United States, including Dayton, Ohio; Denver, Colorado; Evansville, Indiana; Newark, New Jersey; and New York, New York.
